'''Aleo''' is an [[Italian language|Italian]] ([[Sicilian language|Sicilian]]) habitational name varying as Alì or Aleo in Messina province, recorded in medieval [[Latin]] as Aleum (the place name being derived from [[Arabic language|Arabic]] 'ālī ‘high’).

The name is also derivative from the [[Latin]] word "[[gambler]]"

